<title>AHSFMA Pool Rules-2015-web-site.doc</title><meta content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" http-equiv="content-type"><p class="c2 c9"><span class="c0 c8 c13">Auburn Hills Swimming Facility Master Association (AHSFMA) &ndash; Pool Rules</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">All members of the AHSFMA should be able to use the pool and clubhouse facilities in a safe and enjoyable manner. To clarify the existing pool rules and regulations, the following actions were adopted and approved by the AHSFMA Board of Directors.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">1. There will be no lifeguard on duty. Therefore, persons using the pool and pool area do so at their own risk. </span><span class="c0 c8">Wichita City Codes requires that &ldquo;children under the age of 16 must be accompanied by an adult (18 years of age, parent or guardian)&rdquo;</span><span class="c0">. Failure to comply with this rule will result in immediate suspension of pool access for 15 days.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">2. The Auburn Hills Swimming Facilities Master Association pools are PRIVATE and reserved for the use of members and their guests only. </span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">3. A member must accompany all guests. The maximum number of guest per household is five (5) except when the pool is reserved for a private party.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">4. All pools will open 10:00 a.m. and close at 10:00 p.m. &nbsp;Access cards will not open gates before 10:00 a.m. or after 10:00 p.m. &nbsp;Security System will be activated. &nbsp;</span><span class="c7 c0">Do Not</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;prop open the gates.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">5. Suntan oil is prohibited in all pools. </span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">6. Per state law, persons with infections, open sores or communicable diseases will not be allowed in the pools.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">7. Proper swimming attire is required (no cut-off jeans, etc.)</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">8. Loud music, running, rough play, splashing outside pool, cannonball jumping, standing on or jumping from shoulders, towel flipping, dunking, foul language, or &ldquo;crying wolf&rdquo; will not be tolerated.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">9. Eating, drinking, or gum chewing is not permitted while in the water. &nbsp;No towels allowed in the water.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">10. NO SMOKING in the pool area.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">11. The use of pools toys (air mattresses and tubes) will be supervised with discretion. &nbsp;Do not throw hard or sharp objects that could damage pool liner. (Example: toy torpedoes and toy rockets)</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">12. No pets, bikes or skateboards are allowed inside the pool fence. Bikes should be parked outside the pool area and off the sidewalks.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">13. NO GLASS or ALCOHOLIC beverages are allowed in the pool area. All beverages, lotions, etc. must be in unbreakable containers. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">14. No one should be in the pool(s) during a thunderstorm or while it is lightning.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c0 c5"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">15. The Master Pool Association is not responsible for personal property.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">16. Reservations for the Pool </span><span class="c0 c8">do not </span><span class="c0">include the clubhouse, unless reserved on a separate clubhouse reservation form. &nbsp;A Pool Reservation Form must be completed and submitted before a pool may be reserved. &nbsp;</span><span class="c0 c7">Reservations cannot be made until dues are paid in full. &nbsp;Reservation cannot be made more than 90 days in advance of the event date. </span><span class="c0 c8">&nbsp;T</span><span class="c0">he Enclave pool may be reserved for private parties on Sunday evening. &nbsp;The Fairways pool may be reserved for private parties on Friday evening. The Legends and Meadows pool may be reserved for private parties on Saturday evenings. All pool reservations are between 5:00p.m. until 10:00p.m. &nbsp;The pool must be reserved in advance and the member hosting the party is responsible for cleaning pool area after the party. &nbsp;Each AHSFMA member may reserve one unit, one time annually free of charge. &nbsp;All additional reservations of </span><span class="c7 c0 c8">each</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;unit are $75.00. &nbsp;Please reference Clubhouse Rules and Regulations for details on reserving the Clubhouses. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">17. Damage to the pool, liner or furniture will be the responsibility of the member hosting the party.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">18. Anyone who violates the rules will be subject to loss of pool privileges.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">19. The last person to leave the pool area should ensure the restroom lights are off, restroom door and pool gates are locked before leaving. All trash in the pool area should be picked up.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">20. The pool member and/or guests shall provide their name and address upon request.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">21. There will be a $25 charge for replacing a lost pool card.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">22. Any person caught vandalizing the property, equipment or vending machines will be prosecuted.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">23. The pool privileges of any member whose pool dues or other assessments are delinquent may have their pool privileges suspended.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">24. Pool Key activation will occur once a week during pool season on Friday morning prior to 9:00am. &nbsp;To allow entry on Friday and afterward, any member&rsquo;s account must be paid in full by 3:00p.m. on Thursday. &nbsp;There are no exceptions to this policy and no temporary badges will be issued.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2 c9"><span class="c13 c0 c8">POOL RULES ENFORCEMENT</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Each AHSFMA member is expected to ensure that the members of their family and guests are following the pool rules. The elected board members and committee members of the Auburn Hills Master Swimming Facility Association are responsible for the enforcement of the rules.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0 c8">To report a pool rule violation, the following steps should be taken:</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">1. Document the violation(s) including the name(s) of the person(s) committing the violation, and those who witnessed the violation(s). Include the date and the time of the occurrence and briefly describe the rule(s) violation, print and sign your name.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">2. Email to Rodney Wright at </span><span class="c7 c0 c10"><a class="c1" href="mailto:rzwright@homeownermgmt.com">rzwright@homeownermgmt.com</a></span><span class="c0">&nbsp;or Mail to Auburn Hills Swimming Facilities Master Association, C/O HOA Management Services, 900 N. Tyler, Ste. 7, Wichita, KS 67212. </span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">The Board of Directors will review the documented violations. Homeowners that have been cited for a pool or clubhouse rule(s) violation will be invited to attend the meeting when the Board reviews the violation(s).</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Violations that are upheld by the Board of Directors will be confirmed in writing to the homeowner involved, as well as the homeowner reporting the violation.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">If the homeowner or their guests are determined to be in violation of the pool rules a total of three times, their pool privileges will be suspended for a period of one year from the date of the last occurrence.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Any homeowner who continues to use the pool or clubhouse facilities after their pool or clubhouse privileges have been suspended by the Board of Directors will be subject to a $500 fine assessed to the homeowner by the Auburn Hills Swimming Facilities Master Association, as well as any and all necessary legal cost to enforce the suspension and fine.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c5 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c13 c0 c8">If you are threatened, feel in danger or witness vandalism - CALL 911. Record the person&rsquo;s description, vehicle type &amp; tag number. </span></p><div><p class="c2 c9 c11"><span class="c3 c0">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;AHSFMA Pool Rules &ndash; Revised 3-09-2015</span></p>
                  </td>
